              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "* Package Manager: maven\n* Vulnerable module: org.apache.struts.xwork:xwork-core\n* Introduced through: io.github.snyk:todolist-web-struts@0.0.1, org.apache.struts:struts2-core@2.3.20 and others\n### Detailed paths\n* _Introduced through_: io.github.snyk:todolist-web-struts@0.0.1 › org.apache.struts:struts2-core@2.3.20 › org.apache.struts.xwork:xwork-core@2.3.20\n# Overview\n[org.apache.struts.xwork:xwork-core](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.struts.xwork/xwork-core) is a generic command pattern framework. It forms the core of Struts 2.\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to Improper Input Validation via a `%{}` sequence in a tag attribute, aka forced double OGNL evaluation.\n# Remediation\nUpgrade `org.apache.struts.xwork:xwork-core` to version 2.3.28 or higher.\n# References\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/apache/struts/commit/15857a69e7baf3675804495a5954cd0756ac8364)\n"
